n interests and agenda. The central thesis of Overcoming Managerialism is that resisting and overcoming managerialism necessitates the re-establishing of the conceptual distinction between power and authority. Second, it requires the rehabilitating of authoritative management as a protection against authoritarian practices. Authority, properly conceived, redirects power to technical experts and professionals and thereby limits managerial power. The authors discuss ten contentions which, taken together, represent a theory of the foundation of management in which authority, power and rhetoric are central concepts. This book combines academic scholarship with a readable critique of managerialism. It will be of interest to both management scholars and students.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aDelegation of authority. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Management.2bisacsh  aAuthority.  aManagement Education.  aManagerialism.  aPhilosophy of Management.  aPower.1 aJoullié, Jean-Etienne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2022 Englishz978311099282308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2022z9783110992922oZDB-23-DBV0 cEPUBz97831107583370 cprintz978311075816040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311075828340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110758283423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110758283/original  a978-3-11-099282-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLET